'''IC 1011''' is a compact [[elliptical galaxy]]<ref>[http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/cgi-bin/nph-datasearch?search_type=Note_id&objid=37978&objname=IC%201011&img_stamp=YES&hconst=73.0&omegam=0.27&omegav=0.73&corr_z=1&of=table NASA/Caltech Notes for object IC 1011], [[NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database]]</ref> with [[apparent magnitude]] of 14.7,<ref name=NASA/> and with a redshift of z=0.02564 (SIMBAD)<ref name=SIMBAD/> or 0.025703 (NASA),<ref name=NASA>[http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/cgi-bin/nph-objsearch?objname=IC+1011 NED results for object IC 1011], [[NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database]]</ref> yielding a distance of 100 to 120 [[Megaparsecs]].<ref name=NASA/> Its light has taken 349.5 million years to travel to Earth. IC 1011's calculated age is approximately 12.95 billion years.<ref name=NASA/> The IC designation comes from the [[Index Catalogue]].

